# Post migration cleanup brief

Please clean up all the index.md pages under content/blog/, except for content/blog/asia-2009/. Please inspect each markdown page and make the following changes. Before and after examples have been included.

## Remove duplicate blank lines

Replace multiple blank lines with a single blank line. "Blank lines" include any lines that only has a single space or a just a <br> tab.

**Before**

```markdown
No mayonnaise in sight. Fillings seem to get a bit gooey-er the further west you go. Breads range from your standard sliced stuff to the ever-popular focaccia and soft baguettes. The one consistent factor is size — enormous.

<br> 



{{< img-caption src="adelaide-002.jpg" caption="A water mill. Pretentious wine tasters to be found inside" alt="" >}}
```

**After**

```markdown
No mayonnaise in sight. Fillings seem to get a bit gooey-er the further west you go. Breads range from your standard sliced stuff to the ever-popular focaccia and soft baguettes. The one consistent factor is size — enormous.

{{< img-caption src="adelaide-002.jpg" caption="A water mill. Pretentious wine tasters to be found inside" alt="" >}}
```

## Replace emphasis with level 3 heading

Replace instances of a single line of text surrounded with double or triple asterisks with a level 3 heading.

**Before**

```markdown
Every 20 or 30 miles or so, you'll see a sign with something to the effect of -

**Welcome to Beltbuckle**

A *tidy* town
```

**After**

```markdown
Every 20 or 30 miles or so, you'll see a sign with something to the effect of -

### Welcome to Beltbuckle

A *tidy* town
```

